1
00:02:22,810 --> 00:02:23,811
Here.

2
00:02:45,967 --> 00:02:48,301
Huh?

3
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:37,985
Arco!

4
00:03:39,954 --> 00:03:41,656
Ugh, another plant?

5
00:03:42,156 --> 00:03:43,558
What'd you think we were
bringing back?

6
00:03:43,658 --> 00:03:45,593
-A dinosaur?
-Did you see any?

7
00:03:45,693 --> 00:03:47,595
- A mother triceratops.
- Whoa!

8
00:03:47,862 --> 00:03:50,832
She was huge! She would
call her babies like this:

9
00:03:51,165 --> 00:03:52,533
Rarrr!

10
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:54,267
And that's where Ada
found the fern,

11
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:56,003
or else we probably
wouldn't have noticed it.

12
00:03:56,104 --> 00:03:57,739
- Did you pet them?
- Pet them?

13
00:03:57,839 --> 00:04:00,074
Are you kidding?
We were way too scared.

14
00:04:00,174 --> 00:04:03,111
We hid.
Dad was terrified.

15
00:04:03,544 --> 00:04:05,747
Exactly what I thought,

16
00:04:05,947 --> 00:04:07,548
Dryopteris.

17
00:04:08,750 --> 00:04:10,818
With that, we'll be able
to grow thousands.

18
00:04:10,918 --> 00:04:14,722
Dad? You think
that next time I can go along?

19
00:04:14,822 --> 00:04:16,691
Arco,
we've already discussed that.

20
00:04:16,791 --> 00:04:18,626
-You're too young.
-But if I come, I could help.

21
00:04:18,726 --> 00:04:21,328
Yeah, right, the only thing
he's interested in

22
00:04:21,428 --> 00:04:22,730
- is seeing dinos.
- Ada.

23
00:04:22,830 --> 00:04:24,498
She's right though,
we don't travel for fun.

24
00:04:24,599 --> 00:04:26,234
But I told you I'm ready.

25
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:28,335
No flying before the age of 12.

26
00:04:28,435 --> 00:04:30,270
It's the law.
That's the way it is.

27
00:04:30,538 --> 00:04:32,874
Your time will come.
Don't be in such a hurry.

28
00:07:44,265 --> 00:07:46,634
Woohoo! Woo!

29
00:08:28,576 --> 00:08:31,545
♪ <i>Sunshine, lollipops,</i>
<i>And rainbows</i> ♪

30
00:08:31,645 --> 00:08:34,281
♪ <i>Everything that's wonderful</i>
<i>Is what I feel</i> ♪

31
00:08:34,382 --> 00:08:36,550
♪ <i>When we're together</i> ♪

32
00:08:36,650 --> 00:08:39,186
♪ <i>Brighter than a lucky penny</i> ♪

33
00:08:39,286 --> 00:08:42,556
♪ <i>When you're near the rain goes</i>
<i>Disappears, dear</i> ♪

34
00:08:42,656 --> 00:08:44,525
♪ <i>And I feel so fine</i> ♪

35
00:08:44,825 --> 00:08:47,228
♪ <i>Just to know</i>
<i>That you are mine</i> ♪

36
00:08:47,728 --> 00:08:51,465
♪ <i>My life is sunshine,</i>
<i>Lollipops, and rainbows</i> ♪

37
00:08:51,565 --> 00:08:53,534
♪ <i>That's how this refrain goes</i> ♪

38
00:08:53,634 --> 00:08:56,537
♪ <i>So, come on,</i>
<i>Join in, everybody</i> ♪

39
00:08:56,637 --> 00:08:59,373
♪ <i>Sunshine, lollipops,</i>
<i>And rainbows</i> ♪

40
00:08:59,473 --> 00:09:03,577
♪ <i>Everything that's wonderful</i>
<i>Is sure to come your way</i> ♪

41
00:09:04,412 --> 00:09:07,715
♪ <i>When you're in love to stay</i> ♪

42
00:09:11,986 --> 00:09:14,455
<i>- Are you ready?</i>
- Yes! Yeah!

43
00:09:14,555 --> 00:09:16,057
Now we have our new hats.
Shh!

44
00:09:16,157 --> 00:09:18,192
<i>I heard there were</i>
<i>some newcomers out west,</i>

45
00:09:18,292 --> 00:09:21,929
<i>two of the toughest outlaws,</i>
<i>especially the girl,</i>

46
00:09:22,029 --> 00:09:25,599
<i>who goes by the name</i>
<i>of Calamity Jane</i>

47
00:09:25,699 --> 00:09:29,203
<i>with nails as sharp</i>
<i>as an old pair of talons.</i>

48
00:09:29,303 --> 00:09:32,206
All of the sheriffs out there
are looking for her,

49
00:09:32,306 --> 00:09:34,175
but I'll be the one to find her!

50
00:09:36,844 --> 00:09:38,212
<i>Who do you want now?</i>

51
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:40,948
Do Hook! Hook!

52
00:09:41,048 --> 00:09:42,983
Hook! Hook! Hook!

53
00:09:49,990 --> 00:09:51,792
It was just lightning, Peter.

54
00:09:52,259 --> 00:09:55,629
Don't worry, our house
is protected from the storm.

55
00:10:01,235 --> 00:10:03,604
He won't listen
to anyone these days.

56
00:10:03,971 --> 00:10:06,173
- All he wants is his way.
<i>- That's normal.</i>

57
00:10:06,273 --> 00:10:09,578
<i>At his age, you were a holy</i>
<i>terror too, wasn't she, Mikki?</i>

58
00:10:09,677 --> 00:10:12,213
<i>A real monster,</i>
<i>if I remember correctly.</i>

59
00:10:12,313 --> 00:10:16,217
<i>Go on, sweetheart. Eat your</i>
<i>purée, be good. Do it for Mommy.</i>

60
00:10:16,518 --> 00:10:17,852
<i>And how was school today?</i>

61
00:10:17,952 --> 00:10:19,854
<i>How did your history</i>
<i>presentation go?</i>

62
00:10:19,954 --> 00:10:21,655
OK.

63
00:10:21,755 --> 00:10:23,791
I mean,
Clifford was so terrified

64
00:10:23,891 --> 00:10:25,826
that he forgot the whole part
about the pharaohs.

65
00:10:26,093 --> 00:10:28,129
He was shaking like a leaf,
like this.

66
00:10:30,631 --> 00:10:32,133
Oh, Mikki,
you got the appointment

67
00:10:32,233 --> 00:10:34,135
- for Peter's vaccine's, right?
<i>- Yes,</i>

68
00:10:34,235 --> 00:10:36,737
<i>I'm bringing him in</i>
<i>for his boosters tomorrow</i>

69
00:10:36,837 --> 00:10:38,639
<i>and I went shopping</i>
<i>for Saturday.</i>

70
00:10:38,739 --> 00:10:40,575
<i>Iris is making</i>
<i>a lemon meringue pie.</i>

71
00:10:40,674 --> 00:10:43,277
Mikki! It was a surprise.

72
00:10:44,211 --> 00:10:46,280
<i>Oops. My bad.</i>

73
00:10:46,380 --> 00:10:47,815
<i>Actually, about that...</i>

74
00:10:48,048 --> 00:10:51,352
<i>we can't come home this weekend,</i>
<i>we have too much work.</i>

75
00:10:51,452 --> 00:10:53,454
But... what about your birthday?

76
00:10:53,555 --> 00:10:55,890
<i>Hm, we'll celebrate next time.</i>

77
00:10:55,990 --> 00:10:59,160
<i>We'll try to come</i>
<i>next weekend. OK, baby?</i>

78
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:03,364
<i>"'I'm youth, I'm joy!'</i>
<i>Peter answered at a venture.</i>

79
00:11:03,831 --> 00:11:05,299
<i>This of course was foolishness,</i>

80
00:11:05,399 --> 00:11:07,768
<i>but it was proof</i>
<i>to the unhappy Captain Hook</i>

81
00:11:07,868 --> 00:11:10,572
<i>that Peter did not know</i>
<i>in the least who he was</i>

82
00:11:10,671 --> 00:11:12,673
<i>or what he was.</i>

83
00:11:12,773 --> 00:11:16,377
<i>Which is the very pinnacle</i>
<i>of good form."</i>

84
00:11:17,111 --> 00:11:18,112
And then?

85
00:11:18,979 --> 00:11:21,348
<i>I have to get up early.</i>

86
00:11:21,882 --> 00:11:24,752
- <i>Turn off the light soon, OK?</i>
-Yes, Mommy.

87
00:11:25,419 --> 00:11:27,354
<i>I love you so much.</i>

88
00:11:29,023 --> 00:11:31,526
<i>Goodnight, angel.</i>

89
00:11:31,992 --> 00:11:33,427
Night, Mama.

90
00:12:06,927 --> 00:12:09,230
<i>Everything all right?</i>

91
00:12:10,599 --> 00:12:11,932
I can't sleep.

92
00:12:12,032 --> 00:12:14,368
<i>Make a little room for me, OK?</i>

93
00:12:17,037 --> 00:12:18,906
<i>Tell me what's wrong.</i>

94
00:12:20,441 --> 00:12:22,076
Nothing, I said.

95
00:12:22,176 --> 00:12:23,244
I'm fine.

96
00:12:23,477 --> 00:12:25,379
<i>I'm sure they would prefer</i>
<i>to be with you</i>

97
00:12:25,479 --> 00:12:27,181
<i>instead of the office.</i>

98
00:12:27,281 --> 00:12:30,417
<i>When you're a grown-up, you</i>
<i>can't always do what you want.</i>

99
00:12:31,885 --> 00:12:34,255
Do you think
wishes really come true?

100
00:12:34,989 --> 00:12:36,558
Like in fairy tales?

101
00:12:36,658 --> 00:12:38,325
<i>I don't know, Iris.</i>

102
00:12:38,693 --> 00:12:41,228
<i>But what's to stop you</i>
<i>from trying?</i>

103
00:13:22,403 --> 00:13:24,639
-Hi, Mikki!
- <i>Good morning, young man.</i>

104
00:13:24,739 --> 00:13:26,675
-Late again, huh?
<i>-Iris!</i>

105
00:13:26,974 --> 00:13:28,809
<i>-Clifford's here.</i>
-Coming!

106
00:13:28,909 --> 00:13:31,412
<i>-You're going to be late!</i>
-I said I'm coming!

107
00:13:37,017 --> 00:13:38,520
<i>Be careful on the road,</i>

108
00:13:38,620 --> 00:13:40,154
<i>-you hear?</i>
<i>-</i> Yes, Mikki!

109
00:13:40,254 --> 00:13:42,489
Bye bye!

110
00:13:42,657 --> 00:13:43,857
Hurry up!

111
00:13:44,291 --> 00:13:46,226
Why do you always get
to drive?

112
00:13:46,327 --> 00:13:48,462
-'Cause it's my scooter.
- <i>Iris!</i>

113
00:13:48,563 --> 00:13:51,098
<i>I said to drive carefully!</i>

114
00:13:51,566 --> 00:13:54,502
<i>Ugh, your sister</i>
<i>is as stubborn as a mule.</i>

115
00:13:55,102 --> 00:13:57,037
Isn't that
Mr. Deschmaker's car?

116
00:13:57,304 --> 00:14:00,307
Oh, yeah, it is.
He's gonna flip out.

117
00:14:10,918 --> 00:14:13,487
Where do you think
birds hide during a storm?

118
00:14:13,588 --> 00:14:16,658
I don't know,
I've never thought about it.

119
00:14:17,324 --> 00:14:18,959
I used to wish
that I could be a bird

120
00:14:19,059 --> 00:14:20,861
to be able to fly and be free.

121
00:14:21,895 --> 00:14:24,632
Actually, it must be horrible.

122
00:14:25,032 --> 00:14:26,835
I would want to be a cat:

123
00:14:26,934 --> 00:14:29,970
nothing to do,
you walk around, they feed you.

124
00:14:30,170 --> 00:14:31,939
Cats have it all figured out.

125
00:14:32,707 --> 00:14:35,442
But I don't like cats
because they eat birds.

126
00:14:36,210 --> 00:14:38,312
Did you see
on the news about the fire?

127
00:14:38,412 --> 00:14:41,816
My dad says this time
it's gonna destroy everything.

128
00:14:41,915 --> 00:14:43,884
He says that
every time, Clifford.

129
00:14:43,984 --> 00:14:46,420
We have enough canned goods
to last for months.

130
00:14:46,521 --> 00:14:48,889
-Where are you putting it all?
-In the living room,

131
00:14:48,989 --> 00:14:50,792
in my bedroom, I'm sleeping

132
00:14:50,891 --> 00:14:52,527
-on the red beans.
-Haha!

133
00:14:53,193 --> 00:14:55,963
-See you at lunch?
-Yup, see you later.

134
00:15:00,568 --> 00:15:02,302
<i>The universe,</i>
<i>like all living things,</i>

135
00:15:02,403 --> 00:15:04,773
<i>was born one day.</i>
<i>That day occurred</i>

136
00:15:04,873 --> 00:15:06,974
<i>13.8 billion years ago</i>

137
00:15:07,074 --> 00:15:10,210
<i>in a massive flash of light</i>
<i>we call the Big Bang.</i>

138
00:15:10,310 --> 00:15:13,247
<i>Prior to that instant,</i>
<i>time and space did not exist.</i>

139
00:15:13,515 --> 00:15:16,483
<i>At birth, the universe weighed</i>
<i>just 20 micrograms,</i>

140
00:15:16,584 --> 00:15:18,586
<i>the weight of a grain of sand.</i>
<i>That is an average</i>

141
00:15:18,686 --> 00:15:22,189
<i>of 7.7 pounds less than you</i>
<i>when you were born,</i>

142
00:15:22,289 --> 00:15:24,592
<i>and then like you it grew,</i>

143
00:15:24,692 --> 00:15:27,928
<i>forming galaxies and</i>
<i>our solar system. Yes, miss?</i>

144
00:15:29,496 --> 00:15:30,998
I don't feel well.

145
00:15:31,198 --> 00:15:33,000
May I be excused, please?

146
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:34,769
<i>We only have 15 minutes left.</i>

147
00:15:34,869 --> 00:15:37,070
I have a headache.

148
00:15:38,238 --> 00:15:39,774
<i>All right, go on then.</i>

149
00:15:39,874 --> 00:15:41,175
Thank you.

150
00:15:45,814 --> 00:15:47,347
<i>Right, let's continue.</i>

151
00:15:47,448 --> 00:15:49,450
<i>Four and a half</i>
<i>billion years ago...</i>

152
00:16:03,932 --> 00:16:05,365
Hm?

153
00:17:33,588 --> 00:17:35,188
Are you all right?

154
00:17:36,156 --> 00:17:37,525
That was some fall.

155
00:17:38,358 --> 00:17:40,360
-Did you break anything?
-Whoa...

156
00:17:41,629 --> 00:17:42,797
Hey!

157
00:17:55,643 --> 00:17:57,110
Who are you?

158
00:17:57,210 --> 00:17:58,445
Where are we going?

159
00:17:58,546 --> 00:17:59,681
You're talking too loud,

160
00:17:59,781 --> 00:18:00,682
everyone can hear you.

161
00:18:00,782 --> 00:18:02,182
You're unbelievable!

162
00:18:02,282 --> 00:18:04,084
- What?
- I'm picking this up.

163
00:18:04,184 --> 00:18:05,987
-It's beeping like crazy.
-Let me see!

164
00:18:06,119 --> 00:18:07,454
- Look, it's beeping.
- I got it too!

165
00:18:07,555 --> 00:18:09,456
- Holy smokes!
- We need to split up.

166
00:18:09,557 --> 00:18:11,793
-All right? Dougie!
-Yeah?

167
00:18:11,893 --> 00:18:13,460
-You go North.
-All right.

168
00:18:13,561 --> 00:18:14,963
And Frankie and me,
we'll go South.

169
00:18:15,063 --> 00:18:16,496
Wait, hold on a second.
Really?

170
00:18:16,598 --> 00:18:19,000
-Why am I the...
-It's not all about you!

171
00:18:19,099 --> 00:18:20,868
It's not all about me,
you're crazy.

172
00:18:20,969 --> 00:18:22,336
You go off on your own
over there

173
00:18:22,436 --> 00:18:24,505
and the two of us will...

174
00:18:25,039 --> 00:18:26,808
Huh?

175
00:18:26,908 --> 00:18:27,809
Oh!

176
00:18:29,811 --> 00:18:31,411
Shh!

177
00:18:32,479 --> 00:18:34,882
What do I do? What do I do?

178
00:18:44,257 --> 00:18:46,060
Ah! You're so heavy!

179
00:18:52,867 --> 00:18:55,036
-Ah, hello, sirs.
-Whoa!

180
00:18:59,674 --> 00:19:02,744
Are... are you looking
for the treasure too?

181
00:19:04,512 --> 00:19:05,312
What?!

182
00:19:05,412 --> 00:19:08,049
I mean, I just saw a rainbow.

183
00:19:08,148 --> 00:19:10,417
Don't you know
about the legend?

184
00:19:10,785 --> 00:19:13,121
At the end of the rainbow,
the pots of gold and...

185
00:19:13,253 --> 00:19:15,123
Listen, sweetie,
we're busy, go away.

186
00:19:15,222 --> 00:19:17,659
Don't be so rude,
Frankie, come on!

187
00:19:17,992 --> 00:19:19,694
-Come on!
-Sorry.

188
00:19:19,794 --> 00:19:22,162
Um, little girl, have...

189
00:19:22,563 --> 00:19:25,867
have you seen anything strange
in the woods?

190
00:19:26,801 --> 00:19:27,969
No.

191
00:19:28,069 --> 00:19:29,537
Are you sure?

192
00:19:29,637 --> 00:19:31,371
I mean, uh...

193
00:19:32,172 --> 00:19:33,975
there was that little boy.

194
00:19:34,075 --> 00:19:35,375
Little boy?!

195
00:19:35,475 --> 00:19:37,177
That's right.

196
00:19:37,277 --> 00:19:39,047
He ran off that way.

197
00:19:39,147 --> 00:19:41,181
You can't miss him
with his weird outfit.

198
00:19:41,448 --> 00:19:43,785
-Oh!
-It's incredible!

199
00:19:43,885 --> 00:19:45,352
Was he in a bright costume

200
00:19:45,452 --> 00:19:47,220
with a cape? A cape?

201
00:19:47,320 --> 00:19:49,524
Yeah, with lots of colors.

202
00:19:49,624 --> 00:19:51,425
You think he's looking
for the treasure too?

203
00:19:51,526 --> 00:19:53,460
It has to be him,
you just heard what she said.

204
00:19:53,561 --> 00:19:55,495
A kid with a cape!
Let's go. Hurry up.

205
00:19:55,596 --> 00:19:57,431
Uh, goodbye. Thanks, miss.

206
00:19:57,532 --> 00:19:59,299
-Come on, no time!
-Thanks so much, madam.

207
00:19:59,399 --> 00:20:01,301
Now what's the plan?

208
00:20:01,401 --> 00:20:03,705
Here's the plan,
Dougie and me'll go North.

209
00:20:03,805 --> 00:20:06,206
No! I said already
I do not want to!

210
00:21:09,604 --> 00:21:10,872
Mikki!

211
00:21:10,972 --> 00:21:13,641
<i>I was starting</i>
<i>to get seriously worried.</i>

212
00:21:14,075 --> 00:21:16,443
Can you help me please?

213
00:21:16,544 --> 00:21:18,946
He was really out of it,
then all of a sudden, boom!

214
00:21:19,046 --> 00:21:21,516
-He fainted!
- <i>We have to treat it right away</i>

215
00:21:21,616 --> 00:21:24,417
<i>or else he'll be left</i>
<i>with a very bad scar.</i>

216
00:21:24,519 --> 00:21:26,587
<i>Go get me the first-aid kit,</i>
<i>would you, please?</i>

217
00:21:26,687 --> 00:21:29,157
-Where is it?
- <i>In the bathroom upstairs,</i>

218
00:21:29,257 --> 00:21:31,424
<i>top drawer under the sink.</i>

219
00:21:40,701 --> 00:21:43,971
<i>He's fine, no serious injuries,</i>

220
00:21:44,071 --> 00:21:46,007
<i>just that small boo-boo.</i>

221
00:21:46,107 --> 00:21:47,642
<i>Can I have that?</i>

222
00:21:50,912 --> 00:21:52,680
<i>Let's get to work then.</i>

223
00:21:54,447 --> 00:21:57,285
<i>I think he'll need</i>
<i>at least eight stitches.</i>

224
00:21:57,552 --> 00:22:00,221
Ugh!

225
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:01,923
That's gross!

226
00:22:05,159 --> 00:22:06,761
They're not picking up.

227
00:22:08,196 --> 00:22:09,630
<i>They must be busy at work.</i>

228
00:22:09,730 --> 00:22:11,666
<i>Would you set the table, please?</i>

229
00:22:12,266 --> 00:22:14,334
- Think he's a leprechaun?
<i>- I don't really think</i>

230
00:22:14,434 --> 00:22:15,970
<i>they exist, Iris.</i>

231
00:22:16,070 --> 00:22:17,404
What could he be then?

232
00:22:17,505 --> 00:22:19,173
Did you see his cape?

233
00:22:19,273 --> 00:22:20,641
<i>No idea,</i>

234
00:22:21,108 --> 00:22:23,311
<i>but what I understand even less</i>
<i>is what you were doing</i>

235
00:22:23,410 --> 00:22:24,545
<i>all by yourself in the woods.</i>

236
00:22:24,645 --> 00:22:26,747
I already told you.
I saw a rainbow.

237
00:22:26,848 --> 00:22:29,617
<i>Iris, I know</i>
<i>you're bored in class,</i>

238
00:22:29,717 --> 00:22:31,384
<i>but you can't just leave school</i>
<i>like that.</i>

239
00:22:31,652 --> 00:22:33,955
Isn't a little boy who falls
from the sky important?

240
00:22:34,421 --> 00:22:36,257
<i>Little boys don't fall</i>
<i>from the sky.</i>

241
00:22:36,356 --> 00:22:38,092
<i>I think he must be a wizard.</i>

242
00:22:38,192 --> 00:22:39,560
<i>Or maybe an angel.</i>

243
00:22:39,660 --> 00:22:42,063
<i>You can ask him about it</i>
<i>when he wakes up.</i>

244
00:22:44,765 --> 00:22:46,399
We've been going
in circles for three hours.

245
00:22:46,499 --> 00:22:48,536
- This is useless!
- I don't understand.

246
00:22:48,636 --> 00:22:49,704
The signal is weaker now,

247
00:22:49,804 --> 00:22:51,906
but the machine says it's here.

248
00:22:52,472 --> 00:22:54,675
Your machine's
never worked, Dougie.

249
00:22:54,942 --> 00:22:57,444
It's trash. I give up.

250
00:22:57,545 --> 00:23:00,314
She was kinda weird,
the little girl.

251
00:23:00,413 --> 00:23:02,650
We might as well
face reality, huh?

252
00:23:02,750 --> 00:23:05,186
We've been wasting our time
for 20 years.

253
00:23:05,452 --> 00:23:07,387
- Huh? Hey, guys!
- Yeah?

254
00:23:07,487 --> 00:23:09,456
- What?
- Look at that.

255
00:23:14,528 --> 00:23:16,831
- Ah!
- What... what is it?

256
00:23:18,165 --> 00:23:21,168
I don't know, but
I don't think it's from here.

257
00:23:34,782 --> 00:23:35,883
Arco?

258
00:23:40,721 --> 00:23:41,989
Arco?

259
00:23:43,557 --> 00:23:45,126
What's going on?

260
00:23:47,194 --> 00:23:48,495
Arco?!

261
00:23:54,535 --> 00:23:56,504
Arco?

262
00:23:56,604 --> 00:23:58,739
No, no, no! No!

263
00:23:59,173 --> 00:24:00,174
Arco!

264
00:24:00,274 --> 00:24:02,043
Arco!

265
00:24:10,017 --> 00:24:11,118
You all right?

266
00:24:11,552 --> 00:24:13,854
Do you remember me
from the woods?

267
00:24:14,255 --> 00:24:16,757
What's your name?
Mine's Iris.

268
00:24:18,092 --> 00:24:20,261
Um, what year is it?

269
00:24:20,561 --> 00:24:21,796
Well...

270
00:24:22,530 --> 00:24:23,965
it's 2075.

271
00:24:24,065 --> 00:24:26,934
My parents are gonna kill me.

272
00:24:28,102 --> 00:24:29,303
Where are you from?

273
00:24:29,403 --> 00:24:31,639
My flying suit! Where is it?

274
00:24:32,373 --> 00:24:33,341
In the machine.

275
00:24:33,441 --> 00:24:34,809
The what?

276
00:24:34,909 --> 00:24:36,911
- The washing machine.
- Give it back!

277
00:24:37,011 --> 00:24:38,612
-Now!
-OK, OK.

278
00:24:39,046 --> 00:24:41,649
Wait for me here,
I'll be right back.

279
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:54,662
Huh?

280
00:25:25,393 --> 00:25:26,994
Oh, wow!

281
00:25:37,104 --> 00:25:38,672
Huh?

282
00:25:45,046 --> 00:25:47,815
<i>You had eight stitches.</i>

283
00:25:47,915 --> 00:25:49,917
<i>They'll gradually dissolve.</i>

284
00:25:50,017 --> 00:25:51,318
Calm down.

285
00:25:51,419 --> 00:25:53,421
It won't hurt you. It's Mikki.

286
00:25:53,821 --> 00:25:55,322
It took care of you.

287
00:25:55,423 --> 00:25:56,791
<i>What's your name?</i>

288
00:25:58,159 --> 00:25:59,293
Arco.

289
00:25:59,393 --> 00:26:01,195
<i>Arco what?</i>

290
00:26:01,495 --> 00:26:03,064
Arco Dorell.

291
00:26:04,298 --> 00:26:05,566
<i>You don't exist.</i>

292
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:07,868
- <i>You don't...</i>
-But Mikki, he's right here.

293
00:26:12,106 --> 00:26:14,075
Mikki,
what's the matter with you?

294
00:26:16,577 --> 00:26:18,547
Mikki, are you there?

295
00:26:20,581 --> 00:26:22,917
Whoa, you made it crash.

296
00:26:23,017 --> 00:26:24,418
Is it dead?

297
00:26:24,519 --> 00:26:26,187
Of course not.
Robots don't die.

298
00:26:27,522 --> 00:26:28,956
Come on, Mikki.

299
00:26:29,056 --> 00:26:30,224
Restart.

300
00:26:30,525 --> 00:26:31,926
Well, it looks dead.

301
00:26:32,026 --> 00:26:34,128
Come on, help me put it
on the sofa.

302
00:26:37,631 --> 00:26:39,500
-It's heavy!
-I know.

303
00:26:39,600 --> 00:26:41,168
It's an old model.

304
00:26:47,875 --> 00:26:49,076
What kind of robot do you have?

305
00:26:50,010 --> 00:26:51,345
Uh, um...

306
00:26:52,246 --> 00:26:54,014
You don't have a robot?

307
00:26:54,115 --> 00:26:55,382
How do you manage?

308
00:26:55,483 --> 00:26:58,085
Who cleans up after you,
does the laundry, makes meals?

309
00:26:58,185 --> 00:26:59,820
Well, we do.

310
00:27:00,254 --> 00:27:01,789
So, where are you from?

311
00:27:07,995 --> 00:27:10,565
It's the insurance bots.
They can't see you.

312
00:27:11,098 --> 00:27:12,833
Hide in here
and don't move a muscle.

313
00:27:12,933 --> 00:27:14,969
But... but I can't stay here!

314
00:27:15,069 --> 00:27:17,506
- OK! OK!
- I have to leave!

315
00:27:17,606 --> 00:27:18,973
Don't fly away.

316
00:27:22,877 --> 00:27:25,679
<i>Good morning, miss.</i>
<i>We've been alerted to a bug</i>

317
00:27:25,779 --> 00:27:27,181
<i>affecting your nanny bot Mikki,</i>

318
00:27:27,281 --> 00:27:30,619
<i>serial number 28976.</i>
<i>Is that correct?</i>

319
00:27:30,718 --> 00:27:32,319
Yeah, that's right.
It's in the living room.

320
00:27:32,419 --> 00:27:34,922
<i>Can you describe to us</i>
<i>precisely what happened?</i>

321
00:27:35,356 --> 00:27:38,759
Uh, I don't know yet,
it just started to say nonsense.

322
00:27:38,859 --> 00:27:40,861
<i>There have been many errors</i>
<i>in the region,</i>

323
00:27:40,961 --> 00:27:43,464
<i>312 exactly,</i>
<i>because of the storm.</i>

324
00:27:43,565 --> 00:27:45,432
<i>-How long have you had it?</i>
-Forever.

325
00:27:46,300 --> 00:27:47,801
Do you think it's serious?

326
00:27:48,169 --> 00:27:51,138
<i>My coworker will now implement</i>
<i>the standard check-up.</i>

327
00:27:51,238 --> 00:27:52,673
<i>It should only take</i>
<i>a few minutes.</i>

328
00:27:53,741 --> 00:27:55,142
<i>May I?</i>

329
00:28:03,984 --> 00:28:05,986
<i>I think we have a 404.</i>

330
00:28:07,522 --> 00:28:08,889
Is it bad?

331
00:28:08,989 --> 00:28:11,626
<i>No need to worry,</i>
<i>it should be reparable.</i>

332
00:28:12,026 --> 00:28:13,360
Do you know
how long it will take?

333
00:28:13,662 --> 00:28:15,062
<i>It's impossible to say.</i>

334
00:28:15,162 --> 00:28:18,132
<i>Our service has been overbooked</i>
<i>since yesterday.</i>

335
00:28:27,808 --> 00:28:29,043
Oh, no.

336
00:28:31,680 --> 00:28:34,481
No, no, no!

337
00:29:45,953 --> 00:29:47,454
Do you understand
what they're saying?

338
00:29:48,989 --> 00:29:51,358
They're saying
you're a good person.

339
00:29:59,734 --> 00:30:01,969
They're usually hard on us.

340
00:30:13,013 --> 00:30:15,750
Iris, my diamond,
give it back to me.

341
00:30:16,083 --> 00:30:17,918
- What?
- There was a diamond

342
00:30:18,018 --> 00:30:19,486
on my flying suit.

343
00:30:19,587 --> 00:30:21,055
I didn't see a diamond.

344
00:30:21,322 --> 00:30:23,190
Maybe you lost it
when you fell in the woods?

345
00:30:23,290 --> 00:30:25,727
Then let's go back there
right now.

346
00:30:25,826 --> 00:30:28,495
OK, but tell me
where you're from.

347
00:30:28,996 --> 00:30:30,732
-I can't.
- No problem.

348
00:30:30,831 --> 00:30:32,299
-Good luck then.
-Wait!

349
00:30:33,033 --> 00:30:34,501
I can't go home without it.

350
00:30:35,235 --> 00:30:36,303
Too bad.

351
00:30:36,571 --> 00:30:38,339
That's not cool!

352
00:30:39,273 --> 00:30:41,041
Please, please, please!

353
00:30:41,141 --> 00:30:42,777
Hear that, Peter?
He wants to go home?

354
00:30:43,143 --> 00:30:44,945
My parents will start
to worry.

355
00:30:45,212 --> 00:30:46,648
I'm a little busy here.

356
00:30:46,748 --> 00:30:48,650
Someone just broke my robot.

357
00:30:48,750 --> 00:30:50,652
Hold on, wait, wait!

358
00:30:50,752 --> 00:30:52,186
You win.

359
00:30:52,453 --> 00:30:53,954
I'll tell you.

360
00:30:54,823 --> 00:30:56,490
Well, um...

361
00:30:59,093 --> 00:31:00,861
I'm from the future.

362
00:31:01,895 --> 00:31:04,064
I thought
there'd only be robots, that...

363
00:31:04,164 --> 00:31:06,634
we'd all become machines
or something.

364
00:31:06,735 --> 00:31:09,103
-There are still humans?
-Well, yeah.

365
00:31:09,203 --> 00:31:11,539
What's it like? Go on, tell!

366
00:31:11,639 --> 00:31:13,974
Are the ice caps melted?
Are there still koalas?

367
00:31:14,074 --> 00:31:16,076
Oh, I love koalas,
they're so cute,

368
00:31:16,176 --> 00:31:17,812
but apparently
they're nasty to each other.

369
00:31:17,911 --> 00:31:19,748
Uh, can we please go now?

370
00:31:19,848 --> 00:31:21,382
Yeah, no problem.

371
00:31:22,650 --> 00:31:25,252
But, uh, not in that outfit.

372
00:31:36,263 --> 00:31:39,199
What are those poles
with wires going everywhere?

373
00:31:39,299 --> 00:31:41,803
They bring electricity
to our homes.

374
00:31:41,902 --> 00:31:43,303
You don't have them?

375
00:31:43,772 --> 00:31:46,373
No, our houses
are self-sufficient.

376
00:31:46,641 --> 00:31:47,941
What do you mean?

377
00:31:48,342 --> 00:31:49,644
They can make their own energy.

378
00:31:51,945 --> 00:31:54,549
And the little boxes there,
what are those?

379
00:31:55,683 --> 00:31:56,785
Guess.

380
00:31:57,050 --> 00:31:58,686
Bird feeders?

381
00:31:58,787 --> 00:32:00,387
No, not that.

382
00:32:00,487 --> 00:32:03,257
-They're mailboxes.
-"Mailboxes"?

383
00:32:03,991 --> 00:32:05,727
They're for receiving messages,

384
00:32:05,827 --> 00:32:08,462
but we don't use them anymore.

385
00:32:08,929 --> 00:32:10,964
You only really get bad news
in them.

386
00:32:11,064 --> 00:32:13,902
And... your parents?

387
00:32:14,001 --> 00:32:16,905
-Are they dead?
-Huh? No, not at all.

388
00:32:17,271 --> 00:32:20,140
They work in the city
and come back on the weekends.

389
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:22,877
Huh? Wow, you're so lucky.

390
00:32:22,976 --> 00:32:24,445
My parents are always
on my back.

391
00:32:25,245 --> 00:32:27,014
My father's always going,

392
00:32:27,114 --> 00:32:29,116
"Don't do this, Arco.

393
00:32:29,216 --> 00:32:31,452
Don't do that, Arco."

394
00:32:35,690 --> 00:32:37,859
You sure
this is where you found me?

395
00:32:37,958 --> 00:32:39,527
Well, yeah!

396
00:32:39,694 --> 00:32:41,061
What does it look like exactly?

397
00:32:41,161 --> 00:32:43,197
Like a big glass candy.

398
00:32:44,431 --> 00:32:45,600
How big?

399
00:32:45,867 --> 00:32:47,267
About this big.

400
00:32:47,367 --> 00:32:49,704
And what's this big diamond do?

401
00:32:50,037 --> 00:32:51,472
It diffracts lights.

402
00:32:51,573 --> 00:32:53,842
Without it, we can't travel
through time.

403
00:32:53,942 --> 00:32:55,944
Don't you have a back-up
just in case?

404
00:32:56,043 --> 00:32:58,078
Or a plan B?

405
00:32:59,313 --> 00:33:01,181
Um, well,
it'd have to be raining

406
00:33:01,281 --> 00:33:03,383
and sunny at the same time,

407
00:33:03,718 --> 00:33:05,285
but that's very rare.

408
00:33:06,721 --> 00:33:08,489
It's all over, I'm so dead.

409
00:33:09,223 --> 00:33:10,991
Hold on a sec.

410
00:33:11,191 --> 00:33:13,528
I have an idea.

411
00:33:20,133 --> 00:33:21,503
<i>Attention, shoppers,</i>

412
00:33:21,603 --> 00:33:23,505
<i>we'd like to remind</i>
<i>our loyal customers</i>

413
00:33:23,605 --> 00:33:26,774
<i>that the limit is</i>
<i>five identical items per person.</i>

414
00:33:27,007 --> 00:33:30,210
<i>Once again, five identical items</i>
<i>per person.</i>

415
00:33:30,310 --> 00:33:32,379
Wow!

416
00:33:37,117 --> 00:33:38,385
Hey!

417
00:33:38,485 --> 00:33:39,486
Iris!

418
00:33:40,153 --> 00:33:42,089
Oh... hey.

419
00:33:42,189 --> 00:33:43,992
Are you here
to pick up supplies?

420
00:33:44,091 --> 00:33:45,292
Did you see the news?
They're saying

421
00:33:45,392 --> 00:33:47,662
we'll be totally stuck
at home soon.

422
00:33:47,762 --> 00:33:49,664
Clifford, meet me at check-out.

423
00:33:49,964 --> 00:33:52,032
Yes, Dad, coming.

424
00:33:52,499 --> 00:33:53,568
Uh...

425
00:33:53,668 --> 00:33:55,235
Clifford, this is Arco.

426
00:33:55,335 --> 00:33:56,270
My...

427
00:33:56,370 --> 00:33:57,104
cousin!

428
00:33:57,204 --> 00:33:58,205
Arco, Clifford's a friend

429
00:33:58,305 --> 00:34:00,642
-from school.
-Hi, Arco.

430
00:34:01,743 --> 00:34:03,110
Hm...

431
00:34:05,379 --> 00:34:07,815
When someone holds out
their hand, you shake it.

432
00:34:07,916 --> 00:34:09,216
It's the polite thing to do.

433
00:34:09,784 --> 00:34:12,119
Otherwise people start thinking
you're weird

434
00:34:12,219 --> 00:34:14,221
and will start
asking you questions

435
00:34:14,321 --> 00:34:16,658
and you don't want people
asking you questions.

436
00:34:21,896 --> 00:34:24,097
Ah, this is exactly
what we need.

437
00:34:26,133 --> 00:34:28,268
I've never seen
anything like it.

438
00:34:28,368 --> 00:34:30,038
Yeah, well,
it could also just be some piece

439
00:34:30,137 --> 00:34:32,072
of plastic jewelry
the kid dropped.

440
00:34:32,172 --> 00:34:33,575
Shut up, Stewie,
you wouldn't know the difference

441
00:34:33,675 --> 00:34:35,610
between a shard of glass
and an emerald.

442
00:34:35,710 --> 00:34:36,911
Ah!

443
00:34:37,011 --> 00:34:38,145
Am I bothering you, Dougie?

444
00:34:38,245 --> 00:34:39,413
You made me lose my place.

445
00:34:39,514 --> 00:34:41,448
What will you do
with that stuff?

446
00:34:41,549 --> 00:34:43,183
House cleaning,
you ever hear of that?

447
00:34:43,283 --> 00:34:44,719
Do you even know that word?

448
00:34:44,819 --> 00:34:46,219
It's a real pigsty inside.

449
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:47,655
You never put stuff away.

450
00:34:47,755 --> 00:34:49,389
You let everything pile up,
I can't stand it!

451
00:34:49,489 --> 00:34:50,925
Huh?

452
00:34:54,161 --> 00:34:55,495
- Hey, you guys!
- What?

453
00:34:55,597 --> 00:34:57,732
It's the little girl
from the woods.

454
00:34:57,999 --> 00:34:59,299
Go get me the Oxybul.

455
00:34:59,399 --> 00:35:01,069
Oh, right!
Yeah, wait, uh...

456
00:35:01,168 --> 00:35:03,370
-Sorry, the what?
-The sound amplifier!

457
00:35:03,470 --> 00:35:04,939
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah!
Right, right.

458
00:35:07,575 --> 00:35:09,777
I, I, I...
Oh, got it. I got it!

459
00:35:12,847 --> 00:35:14,214
Oh, oh, OK.

460
00:35:14,314 --> 00:35:16,050
I'm getting no sound here.

461
00:35:18,285 --> 00:35:20,287
-My ear!
-Hold on, I gotta adjust volume.

462
00:35:20,387 --> 00:35:21,656
What are they saying?

463
00:35:21,756 --> 00:35:23,625
I can't really hear.
The baby's crying,

464
00:35:23,891 --> 00:35:26,326
but I think they're talking
about the baby bottle.

465
00:35:26,426 --> 00:35:28,563
- Great, that helps!
- Shh!

466
00:35:28,663 --> 00:35:29,496
Shh!

467
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:35,770
It's incredible how calm he is
with you.

468
00:35:36,203 --> 00:35:39,473
With Mikki he's just so fussy.

469
00:35:56,156 --> 00:35:57,659
Your sandwich.

470
00:35:58,826 --> 00:36:00,293
It's my favorite.

471
00:36:00,795 --> 00:36:01,796
Hm?

472
00:36:05,867 --> 00:36:07,769
-Do you like it?
-Mhm!

473
00:36:08,069 --> 00:36:09,871
I was really starving.

474
00:36:16,209 --> 00:36:18,880
It's amazing how different
everything is.

475
00:36:19,179 --> 00:36:21,314
What's it like in your time?

476
00:36:21,616 --> 00:36:23,851
Almost everything is underwater.

477
00:36:23,951 --> 00:36:26,688
The sea has risen a lot
since the Great Fallow.

478
00:36:26,788 --> 00:36:28,790
The Great Fallow?

479
00:36:28,890 --> 00:36:32,527
When we moved to higher
ground to let the Earth rest.

480
00:36:33,193 --> 00:36:35,163
Now we live in the clouds.

481
00:36:35,262 --> 00:36:37,165
The houses are built
on platforms

482
00:36:37,264 --> 00:36:38,733
and anchored to big pillars,

483
00:36:39,167 --> 00:36:42,070
sort of... like giant trees.

484
00:36:42,335 --> 00:36:43,738
Wait a sec.

485
00:36:59,386 --> 00:37:00,588
Kind of like this?

486
00:37:00,688 --> 00:37:03,390
Yes, except our houses
are round.

487
00:37:03,490 --> 00:37:06,527
My sister says
that we live in turtle shells.

488
00:37:08,328 --> 00:37:09,496
And with huge gardens.

489
00:37:09,764 --> 00:37:11,566
Ah, there's static!
I can't hear!

490
00:37:11,666 --> 00:37:13,266
What are they saying?

491
00:37:13,366 --> 00:37:15,203
They're talking
about treehouses.

492
00:37:15,302 --> 00:37:16,771
-What?
-Ah...

493
00:37:16,871 --> 00:37:18,305
What? The fallow?

494
00:37:18,405 --> 00:37:20,307
-The Fallow.
-Fal-what?

495
00:37:20,407 --> 00:37:22,910
-It's fallow. Fallow.
-What's that?

496
00:37:29,083 --> 00:37:30,952
-Like this?
-Wow.

497
00:37:31,251 --> 00:37:33,087
It looks just like home.

498
00:37:33,353 --> 00:37:35,123
You draw super well.

499
00:37:35,790 --> 00:37:38,358
-Can I keep it.
-I'll make you a better one.

500
00:37:39,861 --> 00:37:42,063
I really wish I could draw.

501
00:37:42,329 --> 00:37:45,265
You can express
whatever comes into your mind.

502
00:37:46,466 --> 00:37:48,368
I wish I was able
to talk to birds.

503
00:37:48,468 --> 00:37:51,304
Oh, that's easy!
Anyone can do it.

504
00:37:51,873 --> 00:37:54,509
-Can you teach me?
-What bird do you want?

505
00:37:56,276 --> 00:37:57,912
I don't know.

506
00:37:58,345 --> 00:38:00,047
-Blackbird.
-That's the hardest one.

507
00:38:00,815 --> 00:38:02,049
Then a dove.

508
00:38:04,752 --> 00:38:07,255
- You're teasing me.
- No, I'm not!

509
00:38:07,354 --> 00:38:09,857
- What'd you say then?
- I said...

510
00:38:10,725 --> 00:38:11,993
I like you.

511
00:38:18,331 --> 00:38:20,668
You said something
not very nice.

512
00:38:20,768 --> 00:38:22,770
-Oh, yeah? What'd I say?
-No, no!

513
00:38:22,870 --> 00:38:26,040
- I can't repeat it.
- It's too gross.

514
00:38:33,413 --> 00:38:35,583
No! No, no!

515
00:38:39,386 --> 00:38:41,222
-So, what are they saying?
-Sweet nothings

516
00:38:41,354 --> 00:38:42,322
in bird language.

517
00:38:42,422 --> 00:38:44,292
Huh?

518
00:38:44,391 --> 00:38:45,993
Tell me something in sparrow.

519
00:38:53,134 --> 00:38:54,902
OK, I'm not even gonna try.

520
00:39:01,876 --> 00:39:02,944
Let's go?

521
00:39:04,111 --> 00:39:05,445
Hey, guys! They're moving!

522
00:39:09,150 --> 00:39:10,383
Ah! Argh!

523
00:39:11,986 --> 00:39:14,922
-Ow! Push!
-Hey, get a move on! Hurry up!

524
00:39:15,022 --> 00:39:16,257
You want help?

525
00:39:16,624 --> 00:39:19,026
No, no, I got it. Don't worry.

526
00:39:19,193 --> 00:39:20,695
Go! Go! Go!

527
00:39:20,795 --> 00:39:22,697
I'm going as fast as I can!

528
00:39:22,797 --> 00:39:24,732
Start the van! Start!

529
00:39:27,668 --> 00:39:29,637
No! The other side!

530
00:39:29,737 --> 00:39:32,039
No, that way! That way!

531
00:39:41,515 --> 00:39:43,017
Here we go.

532
00:39:43,117 --> 00:39:44,719
I've emptied the house.

533
00:39:45,418 --> 00:39:47,454
I didn't know
we had this many pillows.

534
00:39:52,827 --> 00:39:54,128
I'll try it out.

535
00:40:03,037 --> 00:40:04,437
It works!

536
00:40:13,446 --> 00:40:15,950
There, this should work.

537
00:40:18,352 --> 00:40:19,687
Hm.

538
00:40:25,259 --> 00:40:26,661
OK.

539
00:40:32,499 --> 00:40:34,869
Well... here goes.

540
00:40:41,474 --> 00:40:43,311
Just in case it works.

541
00:40:44,845 --> 00:40:46,814
We have to say goodbye then.

542
00:40:48,916 --> 00:40:50,284
All right. Go.

543
00:40:50,384 --> 00:40:51,519
Let's do it.

544
00:40:51,953 --> 00:40:54,021
Did you see that
outfit? It's exactly the same.

545
00:40:54,121 --> 00:40:55,323
Hey!

546
00:40:55,690 --> 00:40:58,392
I told you
that little girl was weird.

547
00:40:58,859 --> 00:41:00,328
But they're so sweet together!

548
00:41:00,428 --> 00:41:02,096
Not what we're here for.
Go get the camera!

549
00:41:02,196 --> 00:41:04,532
Why is it always me
who has to do the stupid stuff?

550
00:41:04,632 --> 00:41:06,434
-Hey, seriously?
-OK, I'll do what I have to.

551
00:41:06,534 --> 00:41:08,169
-They're going to hear us.
-Oh, oh, I'm sorry!

552
00:41:08,269 --> 00:41:10,237
-They're going to hear us.
-Shh!

553
00:41:26,454 --> 00:41:27,955
Ready?

554
00:41:28,055 --> 00:41:29,123
Mhm!

555
00:41:29,323 --> 00:41:31,025
On three, you jump.

556
00:41:34,195 --> 00:41:35,596
One...

557
00:41:36,263 --> 00:41:37,365
two...

558
00:41:37,465 --> 00:41:38,232
three!

559
00:41:42,470 --> 00:41:44,071
Ah!

560
00:41:49,643 --> 00:41:51,545
Arco! Are you OK?

561
00:41:51,645 --> 00:41:53,681
Woohoo! Perfect!

562
00:41:53,981 --> 00:41:55,516
-That's wonderful!
-We have our proof!

563
00:41:55,616 --> 00:41:57,585
Wonderful!

564
00:41:57,885 --> 00:41:59,887
I forgot to press record.

565
00:42:00,087 --> 00:42:01,322
-What?!
-No way!

566
00:42:01,422 --> 00:42:02,923
-I'm really, really sorry.
-No!

567
00:42:03,024 --> 00:42:06,861
It was wild, there were
rainbow sparks everywhere.

568
00:42:07,461 --> 00:42:09,296
I felt too heavy.

569
00:42:09,397 --> 00:42:10,564
It'll never work.

570
00:42:11,165 --> 00:42:12,366
Yes, it will.

571
00:42:12,466 --> 00:42:13,968
It's like when I saw you
in the sky.

572
00:42:14,068 --> 00:42:16,437
There was a big trail
behind you.

573
00:42:16,537 --> 00:42:18,105
You need more momentum.

574
00:42:19,306 --> 00:42:20,975
You should jump from the roof.

575
00:42:28,517 --> 00:42:30,184
The same as before?

576
00:42:30,284 --> 00:42:31,619
OK!

577
00:42:52,239 --> 00:42:54,008
Hey, Arco!

578
00:42:54,275 --> 00:42:55,576
You ready?

579
00:42:56,277 --> 00:42:57,845
Yeah, I'm ready!

580
00:42:58,646 --> 00:42:59,880
OK!

581
00:43:00,247 --> 00:43:01,348
One...

582
00:43:02,116 --> 00:43:03,417
two...

583
00:43:03,651 --> 00:43:04,885
three!

584
00:43:41,388 --> 00:43:43,657
Woohoo! It worked!

585
00:43:50,131 --> 00:43:51,265
Arco?

586
00:43:53,400 --> 00:43:55,469
I don't believe it.
You filmed the tree.

587
00:43:55,570 --> 00:43:57,972
You filmed the flora.
You big dummy!

588
00:43:58,072 --> 00:44:00,174
I always told you I didn't know
how to use this stupid thing!

589
00:44:00,274 --> 00:44:02,943
You know what? I'm outta here.
I'm outta here!

590
00:44:03,043 --> 00:44:04,712
See you guys later, <i>sayonara,</i>

591
00:44:04,812 --> 00:44:06,480
<i>auf wiedersehen, ciao</i> !
I give up!

592
00:44:13,787 --> 00:44:15,422
Everything's fine, Peter.

593
00:44:15,756 --> 00:44:17,158
Everything's fine.

594
00:44:18,692 --> 00:44:20,794
He flew away, that's all.

595
00:44:23,697 --> 00:44:25,199
Yeah, in the sky.

596
00:44:25,432 --> 00:44:27,301
Just like that, poof!

597
00:44:28,769 --> 00:44:31,405
I wish he could have stayed
a little bit longer too.

598
00:44:33,073 --> 00:44:34,375
I'm silly.

599
00:44:34,742 --> 00:44:37,077
I should have asked him
more questions.

600
00:44:42,551 --> 00:44:44,785
<i>Hey, hey, Calamity Jane!</i>

601
00:44:44,885 --> 00:44:46,720
My Mikki! Ah!

602
00:44:49,323 --> 00:44:52,092
I have so many things
to tell you!

603
00:44:52,426 --> 00:44:54,596
I wish my life had been normal.

604
00:44:54,695 --> 00:44:56,830
At least now we know
we're not crazy.

605
00:44:56,931 --> 00:44:58,465
But that's not the problem.

606
00:44:58,567 --> 00:45:01,235
It's what other people think.
We're a laughing stock.

607
00:45:01,435 --> 00:45:05,607
Blegh, we're gonna have to go
back and live with Mom and Pop.

608
00:45:05,873 --> 00:45:08,510
I'd like to forget
the whole thing.

609
00:45:14,315 --> 00:45:15,983
Arco!

610
00:45:18,185 --> 00:45:20,287
Arco!

611
00:45:22,557 --> 00:45:24,091
Your cape...

612
00:45:24,458 --> 00:45:25,694
There's not enough light.

613
00:45:25,793 --> 00:45:28,062
<i>This is private property,</i>

614
00:45:28,162 --> 00:45:28,929
<i>young man.</i>

615
00:45:29,029 --> 00:45:30,764
But Mikki, remember?

616
00:45:30,864 --> 00:45:31,932
This is Arco.

617
00:45:34,468 --> 00:45:35,970
<i>Arco what?</i>

618
00:45:44,679 --> 00:45:45,980
Huh...

619
00:45:47,314 --> 00:45:49,016
What's going on?

620
00:45:52,953 --> 00:45:54,556
You never believe me!

621
00:45:54,656 --> 00:45:56,457
<i>Iris, don't speak</i>
<i>to your parents that way.</i>

622
00:45:56,558 --> 00:45:57,992
You're such a tattle tale!

623
00:45:58,092 --> 00:46:00,662
<i>Don't take it out on Mikki,</i>
<i>that's not fair.</i>

624
00:46:00,928 --> 00:46:02,564
<i>I searched in every archive</i>

625
00:46:02,664 --> 00:46:04,699
<i>and he's nowhere to be found.</i>

626
00:46:04,965 --> 00:46:06,934
<i>It's as if he didn't exist.</i>

627
00:46:07,034 --> 00:46:08,269
<i>Well, we're gonna have</i>
<i>to call the police.</i>

628
00:46:08,369 --> 00:46:09,903
- <i>I don't see any other way.</i>
-No!

629
00:46:10,004 --> 00:46:11,839
Dad, please! Please!
We can't tell anyone.

630
00:46:11,939 --> 00:46:14,141
<i>But Iris,</i>
<i>think about his parents.</i>

631
00:46:14,241 --> 00:46:16,110
<i>They must be worried to death.</i>
<i>We have to tell them</i>

632
00:46:16,210 --> 00:46:17,712
- <i>we found him.</i>
-That's just it.

633
00:46:17,811 --> 00:46:19,980
you can't tell them.
That's the whole problem!

634
00:46:20,080 --> 00:46:22,950
<i>Well, sweetheart,</i>
<i>you have to explain why.</i>

635
00:46:23,384 --> 00:46:25,019
<i>Swear you'll believe me?</i>

636
00:46:25,119 --> 00:46:26,954
<i>Of course we'll believe you.</i>

637
00:46:27,454 --> 00:46:28,623
Promise?

638
00:46:28,922 --> 00:46:31,058
-Swear it!
- <i>Iris, please.</i>

639
00:46:31,258 --> 00:46:34,495
There's no way
to contact his parents

640
00:46:34,596 --> 00:46:36,731
'cause, um, technically...

641
00:46:36,830 --> 00:46:38,365
they don't exist yet.

642
00:46:39,066 --> 00:46:41,569
-They're from the future.
- <i>OK, that's enough.</i>

643
00:46:41,670 --> 00:46:43,772
<i>You've got to stop making up</i>
<i>stories for attention.</i>

644
00:46:43,871 --> 00:46:46,874
You see? You never believe me!
I'm sick of it!

645
00:46:46,974 --> 00:46:49,109
And you're never around anyway!

646
00:46:49,410 --> 00:46:52,179
-Liars! Liars, liars, liars!
- <i>Iris...</i>

647
00:46:52,479 --> 00:46:54,716
<i>If there's one thing</i>
<i>I can't stand, it's lying.</i>

648
00:46:55,015 --> 00:46:56,884
<i>Don't you think you took it</i>
<i>a bit too far?</i>

649
00:46:56,984 --> 00:46:58,485
<i>No, I'm sorry.</i>
<i>We're still her parents.</i>

650
00:46:58,586 --> 00:47:00,287
<i>Well, what do we do now?</i>

651
00:47:00,387 --> 00:47:01,989
<i>I don't think</i>
<i>we have a choice.</i>

652
00:47:02,089 --> 00:47:03,824
<i>Mikki, call the police.</i>

653
00:47:04,091 --> 00:47:05,826
<i>I'll take care of it.</i>

654
00:47:08,128 --> 00:47:10,931
We can't stay here!
The police are coming!

655
00:47:11,398 --> 00:47:14,168
We should sneak in when
they're asleep, snatch the kid,

656
00:47:14,268 --> 00:47:15,903
then we can ask him
all the questions

657
00:47:16,003 --> 00:47:18,005
-we want.
-You must be nuts.

658
00:47:18,105 --> 00:47:19,840
You're unbelievable!

659
00:47:19,940 --> 00:47:21,308
No, we're not criminals.

660
00:47:21,408 --> 00:47:23,645
We should go ring
the doorbell now.

661
00:47:23,745 --> 00:47:26,548
We say we're coming
from Child Welfare

662
00:47:26,648 --> 00:47:27,915
and ask to speak with the kid.

663
00:47:28,015 --> 00:47:30,150
The robot will open the door,
moron.

664
00:47:30,250 --> 00:47:32,654
Your story won't last
two minutes.

665
00:47:33,220 --> 00:47:35,389
Are you all right?

666
00:47:37,157 --> 00:47:38,125
Huh?

667
00:47:43,030 --> 00:47:45,199
-Huh?
-What was that?

668
00:47:47,301 --> 00:47:48,737
I don't believe it,
they're getting away!

669
00:47:48,837 --> 00:47:50,070
Hurry up! Hurry up!

670
00:47:50,170 --> 00:47:52,607
-Right, hurry up! Gotta move!
-Now!

671
00:47:57,945 --> 00:48:00,080
- Where are we going?
- To my school.

672
00:48:08,823 --> 00:48:09,858
Stop!

673
00:48:13,828 --> 00:48:16,430
We'll go through the woods.
Follow me!

674
00:48:21,301 --> 00:48:22,970
Shoot! They've gone off road!

675
00:48:23,070 --> 00:48:24,572
Triple shoot! The police!

676
00:48:25,673 --> 00:48:27,274
Listen, stay calm.

677
00:48:27,374 --> 00:48:29,376
Whatever happens, don't say
a word. Leave it to me.

678
00:48:29,476 --> 00:48:30,944
I'm gonna throw them
off the scent.

679
00:48:31,245 --> 00:48:32,980
<i>Gentlemen,</i>
<i>where are you going, please?</i>

680
00:48:33,080 --> 00:48:34,381
Uh...

681
00:48:34,481 --> 00:48:37,251
We got an emergency call.
We're doctors.

682
00:48:37,886 --> 00:48:39,086
<i>May I see your identification,</i>
<i>please?</i>

683
00:48:39,186 --> 00:48:41,221
Ah, yes, my license, of course.

684
00:48:41,321 --> 00:48:44,692
Uh, I know I have it somewhere.

685
00:48:44,793 --> 00:48:47,127
All right, listen,
I haven't got it on me,

686
00:48:47,227 --> 00:48:48,897
but I, um... It's an emergency.

687
00:48:48,996 --> 00:48:50,431
- All right?
- Dougie!

688
00:48:50,532 --> 00:48:51,965
They're getting away!

689
00:48:52,065 --> 00:48:53,535
This is an emergency, OK?

690
00:48:54,001 --> 00:48:55,402
<i>Iris?</i>

691
00:48:55,502 --> 00:48:57,137
<i>The police are here.</i>

692
00:48:58,972 --> 00:49:00,508
<i>Iris?</i>

693
00:49:02,877 --> 00:49:04,178
<i>Iris!</i>

694
00:49:05,412 --> 00:49:07,047
<i>You can't go outside.</i>

695
00:49:07,147 --> 00:49:09,082
<i>The Bubble Plan is underway.</i>

696
00:49:11,318 --> 00:49:12,854
Listen, officer,
do you really want the life

697
00:49:12,953 --> 00:49:14,421
of a child on your conscience?

698
00:49:14,522 --> 00:49:16,691
Every minute that passes
could be fatal.

699
00:49:16,791 --> 00:49:19,259
- We're nanosurgeons!
- No, neurosurgeons!

700
00:49:19,359 --> 00:49:21,295
-Nano or neuro?
-Nano!

701
00:49:21,395 --> 00:49:23,765
You are a child killer!

702
00:49:23,865 --> 00:49:25,633
What are you doing?

703
00:49:30,137 --> 00:49:31,840
Why did I crash through them?

704
00:49:31,940 --> 00:49:33,307
'Cause you don't know
how to lie!

705
00:49:33,407 --> 00:49:35,075
I do too know how to lie!

706
00:49:35,175 --> 00:49:38,111
Oh, yeah? And you think
we look like doctors?

707
00:49:38,212 --> 00:49:39,914
No!

708
00:49:40,013 --> 00:49:41,014
Yes!

709
00:49:58,031 --> 00:49:59,734
I've never been here at night.

710
00:50:01,268 --> 00:50:03,303
I don't recognize anything.

711
00:50:18,853 --> 00:50:20,354
What are they saying?

712
00:50:23,323 --> 00:50:24,358
Run.

713
00:50:25,125 --> 00:50:26,661
Run away.

714
00:50:27,261 --> 00:50:29,664
<i>Mikki, what's going on?</i>

715
00:50:29,764 --> 00:50:31,031
<i>Hello? Can you hear us?</i>

716
00:50:31,131 --> 00:50:32,967
<i>Iris ran away</i>
<i>with the boy.</i>

717
00:50:33,066 --> 00:50:34,702
<i>I have her GPS location.</i>

718
00:50:34,802 --> 00:50:37,539
- <i>I'm on her trail.</i>
- <i>She's only ten, Mikki.</i>

719
00:50:37,639 --> 00:50:40,040
<i>There're fires everywhere. You'd</i>
<i>better hurry up and find her.</i>

720
00:50:40,140 --> 00:50:42,577
<i>- We're on our way.</i>
<i>- Keep us updated.</i>

721
00:50:59,326 --> 00:51:01,596
Argh, we'll never be able
to ditch them like this.

722
00:51:01,696 --> 00:51:03,998
You got a better idea?
You want to drive?

723
00:51:04,097 --> 00:51:06,601
Why do you take everything
so personally?

724
00:51:06,701 --> 00:51:08,268
Brake! Quick, turn right!

725
00:51:08,368 --> 00:51:09,436
Argh!

726
00:51:32,894 --> 00:51:34,896
Huh?

727
00:51:56,483 --> 00:51:58,385
We lost them, we lost them.

728
00:51:59,887 --> 00:52:01,421
Never been so scared, ha!

729
00:52:01,522 --> 00:52:03,625
-Look at that, you guys!
-Huh?

730
00:52:06,527 --> 00:52:08,596
Wow, wow, wow!
Whoa, whoa!

731
00:52:08,696 --> 00:52:10,064
Haha!

732
00:52:26,914 --> 00:52:28,950
- Hurry up, guys!
- OK, we're coming!

733
00:52:29,050 --> 00:52:30,652
- Relax!
- All I do is hurry!

734
00:52:44,132 --> 00:52:45,232
Hm?

735
00:52:47,735 --> 00:52:49,737
- Don't make a peep.
- Hm.

736
00:52:51,438 --> 00:52:53,340
<i>The mayors of</i>
<i>neighboring towns have agreed</i>

737
00:52:53,440 --> 00:52:55,610
<i>to send reinforcements</i>
<i>of personnel and equipment.</i>

738
00:52:56,144 --> 00:52:59,514
<i>And I've just been told</i>
<i>that two ten-year-old children</i>

739
00:52:59,614 --> 00:53:01,683
<i>went missing this evening</i>
<i>in the Elmwood neighborhood.</i>

740
00:53:01,783 --> 00:53:04,752
<i>Anyone with information,</i>
<i>please contact the authorities.</i>

741
00:53:05,620 --> 00:53:07,387
Come!

742
00:53:08,221 --> 00:53:09,891
<i>Do not intervene.</i>

743
00:53:09,991 --> 00:53:11,659
Huh?

744
00:53:15,195 --> 00:53:16,764
Anyone there?

745
00:53:21,435 --> 00:53:22,770
Iris.

746
00:53:26,206 --> 00:53:29,143
Don't worry,
they're in sleep mode.

747
00:53:29,242 --> 00:53:30,812
This is the teachers lounge.

748
00:53:30,912 --> 00:53:31,846
Hm.

749
00:54:23,497 --> 00:54:27,034
Well, well, well.

750
00:54:27,235 --> 00:54:29,237
You really gave us a hard time,
kids.

751
00:54:29,336 --> 00:54:31,205
Don't be scared.

752
00:54:31,572 --> 00:54:33,574
We don't want to hurt you.

753
00:54:33,908 --> 00:54:37,178
We just wanna know
what the rainbows are.

754
00:54:37,612 --> 00:54:39,914
Twenty years ago,
we saw someone

755
00:54:40,882 --> 00:54:43,718
just like you, kid.

756
00:54:44,552 --> 00:54:46,319
Nobody believed us,

757
00:54:46,554 --> 00:54:48,256
not even our parents.

758
00:54:48,689 --> 00:54:53,194
The doctor said it was
a collective hallucination.

759
00:54:53,293 --> 00:54:55,563
We lost hope.

760
00:54:56,164 --> 00:54:57,632
And then you arrived

761
00:54:57,732 --> 00:54:59,734
in the same outfit.

762
00:54:59,834 --> 00:55:01,102
The same cape,

763
00:55:01,202 --> 00:55:02,670
the same diamond
on your forehead.

764
00:55:02,770 --> 00:55:04,005
-How do you know
about the diamond?

765
00:55:04,105 --> 00:55:05,372
- No, Arco!
- And that's...

766
00:55:05,472 --> 00:55:08,075
why you can't go home,
isn't it?

767
00:55:11,712 --> 00:55:14,314
<i>Chief, Unit 12 called.</i>
<i>We have a problem.</i>

768
00:55:14,414 --> 00:55:16,284
<i>Unknown individuals</i>
<i>have infiltrated</i>

769
00:55:16,383 --> 00:55:17,718
<i>the interior of the school.</i>

770
00:55:17,819 --> 00:55:20,721
<i>I'm responsible for two children</i>
<i>who are inside.</i>

771
00:55:21,022 --> 00:55:22,723
<i>I have to go in.</i>

772
00:55:23,423 --> 00:55:24,759
<i>Let it through.</i>

773
00:55:25,626 --> 00:55:27,161
<i>We can't go in there.</i>

774
00:55:27,862 --> 00:55:31,331
<i>We are going</i>
<i>to activate the units on site.</i>

775
00:55:34,302 --> 00:55:36,336
Huh?

776
00:55:39,941 --> 00:55:42,143
<i>What are you doing</i>
<i>on school property?</i>

777
00:55:42,243 --> 00:55:44,512
<i>Stay right where you are.</i>
<i>Stay right where you are.</i>

778
00:55:44,812 --> 00:55:47,682
If they catch you,
they'll never let you go home.

779
00:55:47,782 --> 00:55:49,584
You're gonna have to run fast.

780
00:55:49,684 --> 00:55:51,819
OK, kids, on three.

781
00:55:52,352 --> 00:55:53,721
One...

782
00:55:53,955 --> 00:55:54,856
Two! Ah!

783
00:56:09,670 --> 00:56:10,905
Cliff! What are you doing here?

784
00:56:11,005 --> 00:56:12,240
I thought you were in danger.

785
00:56:12,340 --> 00:56:14,108
You're the one who did this?

786
00:56:17,645 --> 00:56:19,647
- Tell us the truth, kid!
- Are there a lot of you?

787
00:56:19,747 --> 00:56:21,949
Does the government know?

788
00:56:23,851 --> 00:56:25,586
Where do you come from?

789
00:56:26,419 --> 00:56:27,755
From another planet!

790
00:56:27,855 --> 00:56:29,857
I'm sure that you come
from another planet.

791
00:56:30,725 --> 00:56:33,194
-You're aliens!
-That way!

792
00:56:33,294 --> 00:56:34,896
You are aliens, aren't you?

793
00:56:34,996 --> 00:56:37,298
Think about it, Dougie.
If he was an alien,

794
00:56:37,397 --> 00:56:38,799
he wouldn't speak our language.

795
00:56:41,002 --> 00:56:42,803
Ah, you're from Atlantis, right?

796
00:56:42,904 --> 00:56:44,505
I just come from the future.

797
00:56:44,605 --> 00:56:46,406
From the future?

798
00:56:46,507 --> 00:56:48,576
I was right all along! Ha!

799
00:56:48,676 --> 00:56:50,477
Whoa!

800
00:56:50,578 --> 00:56:52,947
You owe me
a bottle of champagne!

801
00:56:53,047 --> 00:56:54,582
Woohoo!

802
00:56:55,716 --> 00:56:57,585
Haha!

803
00:56:59,486 --> 00:57:01,989
We're heroes, guys!
We're heroes!

804
00:57:02,723 --> 00:57:05,159
I have an idea.
We'll hide in the library.

805
00:57:05,259 --> 00:57:07,628
-No one ever goes there.
-Go! Go! Go!

806
00:57:07,728 --> 00:57:10,164
We gotta move! We gotta move!

807
00:57:10,564 --> 00:57:13,500
Hup, hup, hup! Go on!
Go, go, go!

808
00:57:15,770 --> 00:57:17,939
Go on! Get in! Hurry, hurry!

809
00:57:18,239 --> 00:57:20,074
Wait, wait for me!

810
00:57:20,174 --> 00:57:22,143
- Get a move on!
- I'm coming!

811
00:57:22,243 --> 00:57:23,544
-Haha!
-Go!

812
00:57:29,917 --> 00:57:32,219
I knew he wasn't your cousin.

813
00:57:38,326 --> 00:57:39,961
<i>Nothing in Room 315.</i>

814
00:57:46,701 --> 00:57:48,569
<i>Nothing in the 312 either.</i>

815
00:57:48,669 --> 00:57:49,837
Wait, wait, wait!

816
00:57:50,071 --> 00:57:51,772
So, you can travel
to any time period?

817
00:57:51,872 --> 00:57:54,675
I would go to ancient Greece
or to see the Mayans.

818
00:57:54,775 --> 00:57:56,476
I bet life is sweet
with the Mayans.

819
00:57:56,577 --> 00:57:58,679
The Incas. Sorry,
he gets everything confused.

820
00:57:58,779 --> 00:58:01,481
-Oh, give me a break!
-Guys, stop.

821
00:58:02,984 --> 00:58:05,987
Arco, why have you come
to our time?

822
00:58:06,187 --> 00:58:07,521
This period...

823
00:58:07,621 --> 00:58:10,024
isn't it the worst
of humanity, huh?

824
00:58:10,124 --> 00:58:11,325
Uh...

825
00:58:11,425 --> 00:58:12,693
actually...

826
00:58:13,361 --> 00:58:15,830
uh, it was a mistake.

827
00:58:16,664 --> 00:58:18,733
I didn't really choose.

828
00:58:20,067 --> 00:58:22,502
Did I say something wrong?

829
00:58:27,174 --> 00:58:29,610
Iris, here.

830
00:58:30,544 --> 00:58:32,646
Go give it to him.

831
00:58:44,325 --> 00:58:45,693
Hm.

832
00:58:53,434 --> 00:58:54,869
Hey, kid...

833
00:58:55,803 --> 00:58:57,238
are you a little bit in love?

834
00:58:57,338 --> 00:58:59,206
Ew! No way!

835
00:58:59,740 --> 00:59:02,977
Don't worry about it, Clifford.
Don't worry about it.

836
00:59:03,411 --> 00:59:05,246
I once loved a girl too.

837
00:59:05,514 --> 00:59:07,948
But I never had the courage
to tell her.

838
00:59:08,649 --> 00:59:10,251
What happened?

839
00:59:10,351 --> 00:59:11,852
Nothing.

840
00:59:12,853 --> 00:59:15,189
You know,
when you truly love someone,

841
00:59:15,289 --> 00:59:17,358
no matter if they love you back,

842
00:59:17,458 --> 00:59:19,193
the most important thing

843
00:59:19,293 --> 00:59:21,162
is making them happy.

844
00:59:26,300 --> 00:59:27,201
Here.

845
00:59:28,736 --> 00:59:30,071
Now you can go home.

846
00:59:30,171 --> 00:59:31,272
Thank you.

847
00:59:32,039 --> 00:59:34,308
They're not so bad after all.

848
00:59:34,742 --> 00:59:36,744
-Hey there!
-Ahem!

849
00:59:36,844 --> 00:59:39,180
We're here too!
We're not moving!

850
00:59:39,447 --> 00:59:41,048
I guess this time...

851
00:59:42,283 --> 00:59:43,684
it's really over?

852
00:59:50,024 --> 00:59:51,158
What's wrong?

853
00:59:52,460 --> 00:59:54,862
I'm gonna miss you.

854
00:59:55,629 --> 00:59:57,698
I hate saying goodbyes.

855
01:00:00,601 --> 01:00:02,303
What if I go with you?

856
01:00:02,403 --> 01:00:04,238
That's impossible.

857
01:00:04,605 --> 01:00:05,773
But why?

858
01:00:05,873 --> 01:00:07,808
No one should know the future.

859
01:00:08,510 --> 01:00:09,610
Ever.

860
01:00:11,712 --> 01:00:13,515
-What's that?
-Huh?

861
01:00:13,814 --> 01:00:16,083
The bubble, it's closing up.

862
01:00:16,183 --> 01:00:17,318
Quick! Hurry up!

863
01:00:22,857 --> 01:00:24,959
Go! Go! Go!

864
01:00:44,945 --> 01:00:47,948
For the fallow land!

865
01:01:03,397 --> 01:01:05,634
This is crazy.
They'll never give up.

866
01:01:05,733 --> 01:01:07,168
Go on, Arco!

867
01:01:12,206 --> 01:01:13,674
Wait, Dougie.

868
01:01:16,944 --> 01:01:18,846
What do we do now?

869
01:01:23,717 --> 01:01:26,287
Wait!

870
01:01:31,425 --> 01:01:33,060
Arco, wait!

871
01:01:43,337 --> 01:01:44,606
Arco!

872
01:01:44,805 --> 01:01:46,407
Whoa, whoa!

873
01:01:46,707 --> 01:01:48,442
I wanna come with you!

874
01:01:49,343 --> 01:01:50,778
You can't, Iris.

875
01:01:52,846 --> 01:01:55,482
I'm so sorry. You can't.

876
01:01:57,552 --> 01:01:59,954
Arco! Arco, please!

877
01:02:02,022 --> 01:02:04,758
Don't leave me alone!

878
01:02:06,227 --> 01:02:07,728
Don't abandon me.

879
01:02:12,733 --> 01:02:14,501
It's too high!

880
01:02:16,303 --> 01:02:17,404
I can't make it.

881
01:02:17,505 --> 01:02:19,440
I'll give you a leg up, Iris.

882
01:02:19,541 --> 01:02:21,008
But Clifford...

883
01:02:23,911 --> 01:02:25,446
Do what I tell you!

884
01:03:05,986 --> 01:03:07,888
<i>You can see for yourself</i>
<i>they're in danger.</i>

885
01:03:07,988 --> 01:03:09,557
<i>Let me through!</i>

886
01:03:09,658 --> 01:03:12,192
- <i>Prohibited. Prohibited.</i>
- <i>Look, they're in danger!</i>

887
01:03:12,293 --> 01:03:14,928
- <i>According to safety protocol.</i>
- <i>Iris!</i>

888
01:03:15,496 --> 01:03:17,532
- <i>Let me through!</i>
- <i>Stop, halt right there!</i>

889
01:03:17,965 --> 01:03:20,167
- <i>Iris!</i>
- <i>Halt right there!</i>

890
01:04:02,276 --> 01:04:05,346
We're too heavy! I can't steer!

891
01:04:07,915 --> 01:04:10,317
We have to go higher!

892
01:07:42,897 --> 01:07:43,698
Mikki?

893
01:08:42,189 --> 01:08:43,558
Mikki?

894
01:08:43,992 --> 01:08:45,392
<i>Huh?</i>

895
01:08:49,296 --> 01:08:50,932
Mikki, what's wrong with you?

896
01:08:51,032 --> 01:08:53,367
<i>Ir... is.</i>

897
01:08:54,035 --> 01:08:58,338
<i>Memory... disappearing.</i>

898
01:08:59,907 --> 01:09:02,442
Mikki, what happened to you?

899
01:09:02,910 --> 01:09:05,913
<i>Mem... ory.</i>

900
01:09:07,180 --> 01:09:09,717
<i>Mikki...</i>

901
01:09:11,019 --> 01:09:12,754
<i>leave.</i>

902
01:09:13,554 --> 01:09:15,389
No, please.

903
01:09:16,924 --> 01:09:17,725
Mikki...

904
01:09:19,560 --> 01:09:21,562
<i>Ir... is.</i>

905
01:09:21,996 --> 01:09:24,264
-No!
- <i>Leave...</i>

906
01:09:25,066 --> 01:09:26,901
I'm begging you!

907
01:09:34,709 --> 01:09:36,778
Wake up.

908
01:09:37,310 --> 01:09:38,913
Come back.

909
01:09:48,723 --> 01:09:49,557
Come back!

910
01:09:51,759 --> 01:09:53,293
Please.

911
01:10:27,327 --> 01:10:29,429
Arco, wake up.

912
01:10:30,998 --> 01:10:32,332
Huh?

913
01:10:34,836 --> 01:10:36,269
ARCO
Peter?

914
01:10:37,205 --> 01:10:38,806
We have to leave.

915
01:10:42,375 --> 01:10:43,978
Where are we?

916
01:10:45,713 --> 01:10:46,881
No idea.

917
01:10:55,223 --> 01:10:56,657
Oh, no.

918
01:11:12,006 --> 01:11:14,709
Wait, I'll help you.

919
01:11:17,477 --> 01:11:19,747
Just trying to figure out
how to turn it on.

920
01:11:35,263 --> 01:11:37,999
Ah!

921
01:12:13,568 --> 01:12:15,036
Look.

922
01:13:04,852 --> 01:13:05,753
An owl!

923
01:13:07,521 --> 01:13:09,690
- What's it doing here?
- It found a way out!

924
01:13:13,393 --> 01:13:15,062
Faster!

925
01:13:18,733 --> 01:13:20,935
You feel it?
There's wind!

926
01:14:28,636 --> 01:14:30,470
Oh, hey! We're down here!

927
01:14:32,807 --> 01:14:35,076
-We're down here! Right here!
-Hey!

928
01:14:47,521 --> 01:14:50,191
We're... We're right... here.

929
01:14:51,392 --> 01:14:53,527
We're right here.

930
01:14:53,627 --> 01:14:55,062
Your cape.

931
01:14:56,496 --> 01:14:58,032
Oh, no!

932
01:14:58,566 --> 01:15:00,568
No, no, no...

933
01:15:06,107 --> 01:15:08,676
I've wrecked everything.

934
01:15:10,945 --> 01:15:14,115
All I wanted to do
was to see the dinosaurs.

935
01:15:17,284 --> 01:15:19,153
I don't understand.

936
01:15:19,587 --> 01:15:22,123
Children aren't allowed to fly,

937
01:15:22,223 --> 01:15:23,824
not till they're 12.

938
01:15:23,924 --> 01:15:25,659
But the flying suit,

939
01:15:25,760 --> 01:15:27,895
the diamond, the cape.

940
01:15:30,398 --> 01:15:32,299
They're my sister's.

941
01:15:38,205 --> 01:15:39,508
Know what?

942
01:15:40,007 --> 01:15:42,209
Before you arrived,
I made a wish.

943
01:15:42,309 --> 01:15:43,744
Don't tell it to me

944
01:15:43,844 --> 01:15:45,846
or it'll never come true.

945
01:15:46,680 --> 01:15:47,982
In a way...

946
01:15:48,716 --> 01:15:50,851
it already has come true.

947
01:15:52,186 --> 01:15:55,689
Of course it didn't happen
exactly how I wanted,

948
01:15:56,023 --> 01:15:57,324
but...

949
01:15:57,691 --> 01:16:00,027
I think that one way or another,

950
01:16:00,761 --> 01:16:02,930
both of us are responsible.

951
01:16:21,516 --> 01:16:23,518
Look!

952
01:16:52,046 --> 01:16:53,214
Wow!

953
01:17:22,511 --> 01:17:23,744
Arco!

954
01:17:26,647 --> 01:17:28,449
Arco! Arco!

955
01:17:28,550 --> 01:17:31,018
My little Arco!

956
01:17:33,787 --> 01:17:35,289
Arco!

957
01:17:36,023 --> 01:17:36,924
But...

958
01:17:37,258 --> 01:17:39,628
Arco! My love!

959
01:17:41,530 --> 01:17:43,565
I am so happy to find you,

960
01:17:43,664 --> 01:17:45,866
so very happy!

961
01:17:46,100 --> 01:17:46,867
Mommy?

962
01:17:48,736 --> 01:17:50,171
Daddy?

963
01:17:50,771 --> 01:17:53,407
What happened to everyone?

964
01:17:53,642 --> 01:17:56,511
We searched everywhere
for years.

965
01:17:56,911 --> 01:17:58,412
No...

966
01:17:58,613 --> 01:18:00,814
We traveled all through time

967
01:18:00,915 --> 01:18:02,216
-looking for you.
-No.

968
01:18:03,050 --> 01:18:05,886
But you... you...

969
01:18:14,828 --> 01:18:16,230
Don't be sad.

970
01:18:18,365 --> 01:18:19,733
We've found you.

971
01:18:20,868 --> 01:18:23,804
Everything's all right.

972
01:18:24,471 --> 01:18:26,340
I'm so very sorry.

973
01:18:27,841 --> 01:18:29,143
I'm so sorry.

974
01:18:45,726 --> 01:18:46,927
Hello, young lady.

975
01:18:48,597 --> 01:18:50,030
What's your name?

976
01:18:50,965 --> 01:18:52,567
Iris.

977
01:18:52,667 --> 01:18:54,101
And this is Peter.

978
01:18:54,969 --> 01:18:56,837
Can you say hello, Peter?

979
01:18:57,572 --> 01:18:58,839
Hello, Peter.

980
01:19:00,575 --> 01:19:02,243
Thank you so much.

981
01:19:02,544 --> 01:19:05,680
Without you, we would have
never found our son.

982
01:19:05,779 --> 01:19:08,215
But I don't understand.

983
01:19:08,315 --> 01:19:09,483
The drawings

984
01:19:09,584 --> 01:19:10,951
in the cave.

985
01:19:15,356 --> 01:19:16,890
We must go back.

986
01:19:18,425 --> 01:19:20,695
What are you going to do?

987
01:19:20,794 --> 01:19:22,631
How will you get back home?

988
01:19:22,731 --> 01:19:24,098
Don't worry.

989
01:19:25,766 --> 01:19:27,301
It'll be OK.

990
01:19:31,372 --> 01:19:33,007
Thanks for everything.

991
01:19:33,807 --> 01:19:35,776
Don't forget me.

992
01:19:36,143 --> 01:19:37,311
Never.

993
01:19:39,179 --> 01:19:40,347
Arco.

994
01:19:53,561 --> 01:19:55,429
You didn't tell me.

995
01:19:59,701 --> 01:20:01,302
What was your wish?

996
01:20:07,709 --> 01:20:09,577
I wanted things to change.

997
01:21:50,978 --> 01:21:54,181
♪ <i>Like flowers</i> ♪

998
01:21:54,281 --> 01:21:57,752
♪ <i>Floating in the sky</i> ♪

999
01:21:58,185 --> 01:22:02,423
♪ <i>Your sorrow flies away</i> ♪

1000
01:22:04,826 --> 01:22:11,064
♪ <i>The watercolor in your eyes</i> ♪

1001
01:22:11,398 --> 01:22:15,969
♪ <i>Will paint a brighter day</i> ♪

1002
01:22:18,606 --> 01:22:21,241
♪ <i>What will you find?</i> ♪

1003
01:22:21,543 --> 01:22:24,244
♪ <i>Along the light?</i> ♪

1004
01:22:24,546 --> 01:22:27,682
♪ <i>It feels</i>
<i>Like you're clouds away</i> ♪

1005
01:22:31,553 --> 01:22:34,556
♪ <i>Together again</i> ♪

1006
01:22:34,856 --> 01:22:38,058
